toxins.description:
in cats: When a cat chews, grinds, or crushes the plant material, the cyanogenic glycosides are altered and release toxic cyanide into the body2. Once absorbed, the cyanide binds to ferric iron (Fe
3+
), specifically inhibiting the mitochondrial enzyme cytochrome c oxidase24. This interference halts cellular respiration, completely preventing the cells from utilizing oxygen and resulting in rapid, life-threatening tissue hypoxia (oxygen deprivation)
